description.narrative: The Power of Voices Partnership (PvP) is an influencing programme with the Netherlands Ministry of Foreign Affairs. The programme FAIR for ALL led by Oxfam Novib is five year long initiative implemented jointly with consortium members Huairou Commission, SOMO and Third World Network-Africa (TWN-Africa) aimed at supporting and collaborating with people’s rightful demands towards companies, governments and multilateral organizations for economic, social and environmental justice, promoting global trade and value-chains that are fair for all. The main focus of the FAIR for ALL programme proposal is to support and strengthen CSOs to play their diverse roles; as educators, mobilizers, creators and watchdogs to make trade and value chains FAIR for ALL. In OPT, FAIR for ALL programme aims at contributing to more inclusive and sustainable trade and value chains in OPT and create an enabling environment that respects women and men small-scale producers and their rights, protects the environment and supports youth economic empowerment. The OPT FAIR for ALL programme will be implemented by Oxfam in OPT and partners, aiming to: 1) Advocate for policies that contribute to an enhanced agricultural sector with increased linkages to regional and international markets,focusing on youth, women and women’s rights organizations, cooperatives and women-led businesses; 2) Advocate for improving key regulations (tax refunds, anti-dumping, anti-monopolism, protection of local products, regulating central markets, cooperative laws) that directly impact the agricultural sector andliving conditions of small-scale farmers in Palestine. 3) Advocate for ease of movement for raw and processed agricultural products, trade between Gaza and the West Bank, marketing promotions for buying local products, external trade and export facilitation through supporting trade missions, B2B meetings and trial shipments, cofinancing and incentives engaging the private sector; 4) Advocate for increased budget allocation in the agricultural sector, increased transparency, accountability and reallocation of budgets to respond to the needs of Palestinians in general and the targeted groups in particular; 5) Promote gender equity and gender-sensitive policies and laws by advocating for gender-responsive budgeting at the national and local levels, and to promote women’s rights in the private and public sectors. These objectives will be achieved by strengthening civil society groups, including CBOs, small producers, and cooperatives with greater capacities and knowledge on governance principles, human rights, and social accountability; addressing negative narratives and shrinking civic space with counter narratives to shift the terms of the debate; and strengthening citizen’s activism to create space for CSOs to voice issues. To achieve main objectives of the programme in OPT, Oxfam will collaborate with Palestinian Farmers’ Union (PFU); Transparency Palestine (AMAN); Rural Women’s Development Society (RWDS); Palestine Trade Center (PalTrade).

participating-org.narrative:
Oxfam Novib has been active in the Occupied Palestinian Territory/Israel (OPT/I) since 1982 and working with Palestinian refugees in Lebanon since the mid 1980s. It has built up a strong network of relationships with local NGOs and counts among its localcounterparts some of the largest and most professional NGOs in various sectors. It has accompanied these NGOs in their development from ad hoc volunteer groups to sizeable professional institutions with national outreach. At the same time the conceptualisation of the programme has evolved from three country programs in the early 1990s to a program for Palestinians in the Middle East (PME) working withPalestinians in OPT, Israel and Lebanon.
The programme has changed over the years with the establishment of the Palestinian Authority (PA) in the mid-1990s from a focus on support and service provision at a grassroots level and grassroots mobilization, to working towards influencing the establishment of the PA, its lawmaking and supporting building a democratic state # this involved supporting efforts of Palestinian civil society to build the basis for a democratic Palestinian state with room for civil participation, ensuring inclusion of vulnerable groups, refugees and women, and shaping its laws and systems. Oxfam Novib has also supported partners that are working on the provision of humanitarian assistance, response preparedness and conflict transformation. We have also supported partners in the provision of health services, access to quality education and gender justice.
